mummy, what's the matter?

1065
00:47:02,967 --> 00:47:04,467
you are upset.

1066
00:47:05,333 --> 00:47:06,934
why are you crying?

1067
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:09,400
oh, because you're such a little boy.

1068
00:47:14,467 --> 00:47:15,499
don't cry.

1069
00:47:15,700 --> 00:47:16,666
hmm.

1070
00:47:16,867 --> 00:47:18,500
I needed to tell you.

1071
00:47:19,367 --> 00:47:21,132
it had to happen sooner or later.

1072
00:47:21,333 --> 00:47:23,400
it makes me feel so old.

1073
00:47:35,167 --> 00:47:36,033
"age cannot wither her,

1074
00:47:36,234 --> 00:47:38,400
nor custom stale her infinite variety"

1075
00:47:40,300 --> 00:47:41,499
if I'd been Cleopatra,

1076
00:47:41,700 --> 00:47:43,767
I'd have put whoever said that to death.

1077
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:46,234
[laughing]

1078
00:47:46,767 --> 00:47:48,800
to tell you the truth,
I didn't enjoy it much.

1079
00:47:49,934 --> 00:47:52,000
oh, you're so very, very young.

1080
00:47:54,567 --> 00:47:56,132
I'll grow out of it.

1081
00:47:56,333 --> 00:47:57,600
hmm.

1082
00:47:58,034 --> 00:47:59,467
[laughing]

1083
00:48:04,934 --> 00:48:06,667
I may go abroad for a while.

1084
00:48:06,934 --> 00:48:07,534
oh, where?

1085
00:48:07,667 --> 00:48:09,667
I don't know. Italy, France. abroad.

1086
00:48:18,067 --> 00:48:19,132
I say,

1087
00:48:19,333 --> 00:48:21,100
about--about
that under study,

1088
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:23,667
is there any chance for Joan?

1089
00:48:24,667 --> 00:48:26,467
tell her to write to me.

1090
00:48:28,867 --> 00:48:30,400
thanks. good night.

1091
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:32,934
good night, darling.

1092
00:48:47,734 --> 00:48:49,333
an understudy, my foot.

1093
00:48:53,100 --> 00:48:54,467
[exhales]

1094
00:49:17,367 --> 00:49:18,967
[footsteps approaching]

1095
00:49:21,500 --> 00:49:23,267
wait. hold it.

1096
00:49:27,167 --> 00:49:28,634
[door creaking]

1097
00:49:32,167 --> 00:49:33,967
it's from you know who.

1098
00:49:52,700 --> 00:49:54,434
I don't want to be disturbed.

1099
00:50:05,300 --> 00:50:06,499
good matinee?

1100
00:50:06,700 --> 00:50:07,533
all right,

1101
00:50:07,734 --> 00:50:09,366
but I'm not feeling very well.

1102
00:50:09,567 --> 00:50:11,667
draw up a chair. sit down.

1103
00:50:19,401 --> 00:50:20,400
what's the matter?

1104
00:50:20,601 --> 00:50:22,801
nothing. I haven't been sleeping.

1105
00:50:26,934 --> 00:50:28,834
I had a post card from Roger.

1106
00:50:29,500 --> 00:50:30,100
he's in Naples.

1107
00:50:30,301 --> 00:50:31,733
says he's having a great time.

1108
00:50:31,934 --> 00:50:34,200
yes, but you haven't come
here just to tell me that,

1109
00:50:35,200 --> 00:50:35,966
have you?

1110
00:50:36,167 --> 00:50:38,101
no, it's something else. I, uh...

1111
00:50:40,101 --> 00:50:42,267
I can't pay you back
the money that I owe you.

1112
00:50:43,367 --> 00:50:45,366
I know I said at the end of last month.

1113
00:50:45,567 --> 00:50:47,233
but I just don't have it.

1114
00:50:47,434 --> 00:50:49,034
I could pay it off.

1115
00:50:49,234 --> 00:50:51,334
I hate having to ask
for more time. but...

1116
00:50:51,667 --> 00:50:53,634
don't be such a bloody
little idiot, tom.

1117
00:50:55,401 --> 00:50:56,066
it's so humiliating, Julia.

1118
00:50:56,267 --> 00:50:58,233
geez, when you said
you'd pay my tips for me,

1119
00:50:58,434 --> 00:51:00,266
how do you think that made me feel?

1120
00:51:00,467 --> 00:51:02,334
I said I'm sorry, I didn't mean it.

1121
00:51:02,800 --> 00:51:03,833
I was jealous of you

1122
00:51:04,034 --> 00:51:06,000
spending so much time with Roger.

1123
00:51:10,167 --> 00:51:11,499
I was jealous.

1124
00:51:11,700 --> 00:51:13,467
I was jealous of you going out

1125
00:51:13,700 --> 00:51:15,599
and having a good time without me.

1126
00:51:15,800 --> 00:51:16,966
is that so horrible?

1127
00:51:17,167 --> 00:51:19,367
I should never have
accepted anything from you.

1128
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:24,000
you're everything in the world to me.

1129
00:51:24,334 --> 00:51:24,934
you know that.

1130
00:51:24,834 --> 00:51:27,167
I love being with you.
I don't want to lose you.

1131
00:51:28,767 --> 00:51:30,867
I have few friends. real friends.

1132
00:51:31,967 --> 00:51:33,633
and you're the only person in my life

1133
00:51:33,834 --> 00:51:35,967
with whom I can be entirely myself.

1134
00:51:37,134 --> 00:51:38,433
[gasping]

1135
00:51:38,634 --> 00:51:40,167
let's... let's go...

1136
00:51:42,801 --> 00:51:44,367
[exhales]

1137
00:51:49,967 --> 00:51:52,000
let's go on seeing each other. please.

1138
00:51:55,401 --> 00:51:56,967
oh, Julia.

1139
00:52:32,801 --> 00:52:34,301
[giggling]

1140
00:52:36,701 --> 00:52:37,533
(Evie) well, I've always said,

1141
00:52:37,734 --> 00:52:40,034
you're lucky you can cry
without your eyelids swelling.

1142
00:52:41,567 --> 00:52:42,700
go to hell.

1143
00:52:42,901 --> 00:52:45,134
well, you're looking a lot happier,

1144
00:52:45,867 --> 00:52:47,233
I'll say that for you.

1145
00:52:47,434 --> 00:52:48,466
I hope with good reason.

1146
00:52:48,667 --> 00:52:51,000
if you're thinking what
I think you're thinking,

1147
00:52:51,801 --> 00:52:52,899
then stop thinking.

1148
00:52:53,100 --> 00:52:55,200
all the same, Evie,
you know what I think?

1149
00:52:55,700 --> 00:52:57,334
no, what do you think?

1150
00:52:57,801 --> 00:52:59,033
what mugs men are.

1151
00:52:59,234 --> 00:53:01,334
well, they can't keep
it in their trousers,

1152
00:53:01,734 --> 00:53:03,533
[Julia laughs] that's for sure.

1153
00:53:03,734 --> 00:53:05,334
you're a revolting hag.

1154
00:53:05,634 --> 00:53:07,100
[Julia giggling]

1155
00:53:07,434 --> 00:53:08,466
yes, I am happier.

1156
00:53:08,667 --> 00:53:10,600
everything will be all right now.

1157
00:53:11,334 --> 00:53:13,134
[sighs] I can't help feeling...

1158
00:53:13,500 --> 00:53:14,899
I wish I didn't.

1159
00:53:15,100 --> 00:53:16,934
deep down, I can't help feeling...

1160
00:53:17,534 --> 00:53:18,399
what?

1161
00:53:18,600 --> 00:53:20,534
a certain contempt for that boy.

1162
00:53:21,867 --> 00:53:23,266
he's so transparent.

1163
00:53:23,467 --> 00:53:25,767
life is just a bowl of cherries

1164
00:53:26,801 --> 00:53:28,867
don't make it serious
life's too mysterious

1165
00:53:30,600 --> 00:53:32,767
you work, you save, you worry so

1166
00:53:33,567 --> 00:53:36,201
but you can't take your dough

